Class TextNodeExtractor

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.TextNodeExtractor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.jsoup.select.NodeVisitor

    public class TextNodeExtractor
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.jsoup.select.NodeVisitor
    This is the TextNodeExtractor class. This class is responsible for extracting the text from the content in the List Strings sent by the CrawlerThread class.

      • head

        public void head(org.jsoup.nodes.Node node,
                 int depth)
        This method gets the first seen node of the html document. The head node - e.g the first node to be visited - is the first node in the document as the query is set to null. The head method then retrieves all text nodes and adds them to the List 'strings'.
